88 THE ODEs OF HORACE.

ODE XXVI.

TO L. AELIUS LAMIA.

Horace addresses this same Lamia again, Lib. III. Ode xviii. Lamia must have been very young when this ode was written, the date of which is to be guessed from the refer- ence to Tiridates and the Parthian disturbances. Assum- ing with Orelli, Macleane, and others, that it was composed A. U. c. 729, just before Tiridates fled from his kingdom,

Lamia survived fifty-seven years, dying A. U. C. 786 (Tac. Ann.‚ vi. 27).
